** this verse text was very popular among Abbey manuscripts**

The Charter of the Abbey of the Holy Ghost : a Critical edition from all known extant manuscrpts with introduction notes and glossary Fanning 
Ms. Maidstone Museum 6. Maidstone Kent 
A small book of 59 pages in single columns with 25-27 lines per page of the early fifteenth century. 
It contains: 
1. A hymn "Ihesu thy swetnesse hose miht it se, and thereof to haue a clene knowinge" 
2. A note by James Hinton Baverstich stating that this MS was in the possesion of his ancestors 
3. The Pistill of Love. (Fervor amoris) 
4. The charter of the abbey of the Holy Ghost f.41r - 58v
5. "O rex glorie domine uirtutum qui triumphator mortis super omnes celos...." 
6. "Exortacio Johannis Crisostomi ad quemdam episcopum amicum suum...." 
7. 4 lines at the end. "Si vis saliari semper studeas..." 

